    <description>
      <levelledPara>
        <title>SYSTEM OVERVIEW</title>
        <para>The H2 Refueling System (ATA 02-32-00) provides safe and efficient 
              transfer of liquid hydrogen fuel from ground equipment to the aircraft 
              fuel tanks. The system is designed for cryogenic operation at -253°C 
              (-423°F) and operates at pressures up to 5 bar (72.5 psi).</para>
      </levelledPara>

      <levelledPara>
        <title>SYSTEM COMPONENTS</title>
        <para>The refueling system consists of the following major components:</para>
        <para>
          <randomList>
            <listItem>
              <para><emphasis emphasisType="em02">Refueling Panel (02-32-10)</emphasis> - 
                    External access panel with receptacle door and status indicators</para>
            </listItem>
            <listItem>
              <para><emphasis emphasisType="em02">Refueling Receptacle (02-32-20)</emphasis> - 
                    Quick-disconnect coupling mechanism compatible with ground equipment</para>
            </listItem>
            <listItem>
              <para><emphasis emphasisType="em02">Refueling Valves (02-32-30)</emphasis> - 
                    Main shutoff, isolation, and check valves</para>
            </listItem>
            <listItem>
              <para><emphasis emphasisType="em02">Refueling Lines (02-32-40)</emphasis> - 
                    Cryogenic-rated stainless steel lines with vacuum insulation</para>
            </listItem>
            <listItem>
              <para><emphasis emphasisType="em02">Leak Detection System (02-32-50)</emphasis> - 
                    H2 sensors with neural network processing for leak identification</para>
            </listItem>
            <listItem>
              <para><emphasis emphasisType="em02">Pressure Monitoring (02-32-60)</emphasis> - 
                    High-accuracy pressure sensors and relief valves</para>
            </listItem>
            <listItem>
              <para><emphasis emphasisType="em02">Temperature Monitoring (02-32-70)</emphasis> - 
                    Cryogenic temperature sensors (-253°C rated)</para>
            </listItem>
            <listItem>
              <para><emphasis emphasisType="em02">Ventilation System (02-32-80)</emphasis> - 
                    50 ACH (Air Changes per Hour) forced ventilation for safety</para>
            </listItem>
            <listItem>
              <para><emphasis emphasisType="em02">Grounding System (02-32-90)</emphasis> - 
                    Static discharge protection (≤3 milliohm resistance)</para>
            </listItem>
          </randomList>
        </para>
      </levelledPara>

      <levelledPara>
        <title>DESIGN SPECIFICATIONS</title>
        <para>
          <definitionList>
            <definitionListItem>
              <listItemTerm>Maximum Flow Rate</listItemTerm>
              <listItemDefinition>
                <para>180 kg/min (396 lb/min) at 3.0 bar</para>
              </listItemDefinition>
            </definitionListItem>
            <definitionListItem>
              <listItemTerm>Normal Flow Rate</listItemTerm>
              <listItemDefinition>
                <para>120 kg/min (264 lb/min)</para>
              </listItemDefinition>
            </definitionListItem>
            <definitionListItem>
              <listItemTerm>Operating Pressure</listItemTerm>
              <listItemDefinition>
                <para>2.8 to 3.2 bar (40 to 46 psi)</para>
              </listItemDefinition>
            </definitionListItem>
            <definitionListItem>
              <listItemTerm>Test Pressure</listItemTerm>
              <listItemDefinition>
                <para>5.0 bar (72.5 psi) for 30 seconds</para>
              </listItemDefinition>
            </definitionListItem>
            <definitionListItem>
              <listItemTerm>Operating Temperature</listItemTerm>
              <listItemDefinition>
                <para>-253°C (-423°F) liquid H2</para>
              </listItemDefinition>
            </definitionListItem>
            <definitionListItem>
              <listItemTerm>Leak Detection Threshold</listItemTerm>
              <listItemDefinition>
                <para>10 ppm H2 concentration (25% LEL)</para>
              </listItemDefinition>
            </definitionListItem>
            <definitionListItem>
              <listItemTerm>Safety Zone Radius</listItemTerm>
              <listItemDefinition>
                <para>50 meters (164 feet) during refueling</para>
              </listItemDefinition>
            </definitionListItem>
          </definitionList>
        </para>
      </levelledPara>

      <levelledPara>
        <title>OPERATIONAL MODES</title>
        <para>The refueling system operates in the following modes:</para>
        <para>
          <sequentialList>
            <listItem>
              <para><emphasis emphasisType="em02">Pre-Refueling</emphasis> - 
                    System checks, grounding connection, leak detection verification</para>
            </listItem>
            <listItem>
              <para><emphasis emphasisType="em02">Connection</emphasis> - 
                    Coupling engagement, pressure test, line cooldown</para>
            </listItem>
            <listItem>
              <para><emphasis emphasisType="em02">Refueling</emphasis> - 
                    Progressive flow rate increase, continuous monitoring</para>
            </listItem>
            <listItem>
              <para><emphasis emphasisType="em02">Post-Refueling</emphasis> - 
                    Flow shutdown, line purge, disconnect sequence</para>
            </listItem>
            <listItem>
              <para><emphasis emphasisType="em02">Emergency Defuel</emphasis> - 
                    Rapid fuel removal at 150 kg/min if required</para>
            </listItem>
          </sequentialList>
        </para>
      </levelledPara>

      <levelledPara>
        <title>SAFETY FEATURES</title>
        <para>The system incorporates multiple safety features:</para>
        <para>
          <randomList>
            <listItem>
              <para>Redundant leak detection with AI-powered pattern recognition</para>
            </listItem>
            <listItem>
              <para>Automatic emergency shutoff on leak detection (&lt;2 seconds)</para>
            </listItem>
            <listItem>
              <para>Pressure relief valves (set at 4.5 bar)</para>
            </listItem>
            <listItem>
              <para>Forced ventilation system (50 ACH minimum)</para>
            </listItem>
            <listItem>
              <para>Static grounding verification before refueling</para>
            </listItem>
            <listItem>
              <para>Interlocks preventing operation with open panel door</para>
            </listItem>
            <listItem>
              <para>Thermal protection for personnel and equipment</para>
            </listItem>
            <listItem>
              <para>CAOS real-time monitoring and predictive alerts</para>
            </listItem>
          </randomList>
        </para>
      </levelledPara>

      <levelledPara>
        <title>CAOS INTEGRATION</title>
        <para>The refueling system integrates with the CAOS (Computer Aided Operations 
              and Services) digital twin platform, providing:</para>
        <para>
          <randomList>
            <listItem>
              <para>Real-time decision tree (RTD) support for test procedures</para>
            </listItem>
            <listItem>
              <para>Neural network (NN) models for leak detection and diagnostics</para>
            </listItem>
            <listItem>
              <para>Predictive maintenance algorithms</para>
            </listItem>
            <listItem>
              <para>Digital procedure execution tracking</para>
            </listItem>
            <listItem>
              <para>Fleet-wide learning and optimization</para>
            </listItem>
          </randomList>
        </para>
      </levelledPara>

      <levelledPara>
        <title>MAINTENANCE REQUIREMENTS</title>
        <para>Regular maintenance intervals are defined in AMM_Index.csv. 
              Critical systems require H2-certified personnel. Quarterly calibration 
              is required for leak detection sensors. Monthly grounding resistance 
              testing is mandatory.</para>
      </levelledPara>

